Plot Function fo Data Driven Tests

Source: R/ddst.plot.R
plot.ddst.test.Rd

Plots coordinates for selected test statistics

# S3 method for ddst.test
plot(x, ...)

Arguments

x

result from ddst test function
...

currently not used

Examples

# H0 is true
x <- runif(80)
y <- runif(80)
z <- runif(80)
t <- ddst.ksample.test(list(x, y, z))
#> Error in ddst.ksample.Nk(x.vector, n, d_N = d.n, c = c): object 'd.n' not found
plot(t)
